snippet.title: Dallas Police Now Smearing Reputation of Shooting Victim?
snippet.description:
A white Dallas police officer, Amber Guyger, shot and killed her black neighbor, Botham Jean, after entering his apartment and was charged with manslaughter. The officer had just returned from working a shift and says she was in the wrong apartment. Now, the police department has released to the media accusation he had marijuana in his apartment. The victim’s family is calling this a smear campaign. RT America’s Ashlee Banks analyzes the latest with retired Chief Deputy U.S. Marshal Matthew Fogg.
